post_cb({"bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_21942236_21942353_0": {"length": 23, "quality": 0.9583333333333334, "section_id": 6700}}, "n3337": {"so_21942236_21942353_0": {"length": 23, "quality": 0.9583333333333334, "section_id": 6455}}, "n4659": {"so_21942236_21942353_0": {"length": 23, "quality": 0.9583333333333334, "section_id": 8174}}}, "21942353": {"Id": "21942353", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>The standard says (<code>draft n3337, 11.7 [class.access.nest]</code>):  </p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_21942236_21942353_0\">1 <strong>A nested class is a member and as such has the same access rights as any other member.</strong> The members of\n  an enclosing class have no special access to members of a nested class; the usual access rules (Clause 11)\n  shall be obeyed. [...]</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>And that's pretty much it. <code>C3</code> has got the same access right as, say, <code>methC1</code>.</p>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2014-02-21T18:28:18.370", "CommentCount": "5", "CreationDate": "2014-02-21T18:28:18.370", "ParentId": "21942236", "Score": "4", "OwnerUserId": "947836"}, "21942236": {"ViewCount": "70", "Body": "<p>The following builds in VS 2010: </p>\n<pre><code>class C1\n{\nprivate:\n    enum E {E_VAL};\n    static void methC1() {}\n\npublic:\n    class C2\n    {\n    public:\n        class C3\n        {\n        public:\n            void methC3() \n            {\n                int a=E_VAL; // this surprised me\n                methC1();    // and this too\n            }\n        };\n    };\n};\n\nint main() \n{\n    C1::C2::C3 obj;\n    obj.methC3();\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>Is this standard? I saw this <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/486136/869951\">other SO post</a> where an answer compares inner classes to friend classes, but a friend of a friend is not a friend, so wondering what standard says. </p>\n", "Title": "Inner class access to outer several levels up", "CreationDate": "2014-02-21T18:21:06.773", "LastActivityDate": "2014-02-21T18:28:18.370", "CommentCount": "0", "LastEditDate": "2017-05-23T12:20:57.370", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditorUserId": "-1", "Id": "21942236", "Score": "5", "OwnerUserId": "869951", "Tags": "<c++><inner-classes>", "AnswerCount": "1"}});